        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Before Donation</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4">
            <li>Eat a healthy meal 2–3 hours prior (avoid fatty foods).</li>
            <li>Stay hydrated—drink plenty of water.</li>
            <li>Get a good night’s sleep.</li>
            <li>Avoid alcohol for 24 hours.</li>
            <li>Bring a valid ID and know your medical history.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">During Donation</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4">
            <li>Inform staff of any discomfort or concerns.</li>
            <li>Relax and follow the phlebotomist’s instructions.</li>
            <li>The process takes about 10–15 minutes.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">After Donation</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mb-4">
            <li>Rest for 10–15 minutes and have refreshments.</li>
            <li>Avoid heavy lifting or strenuous exercise for 24 hours.</li>
            <li>Drink extra fluids for the next 48 hours.</li>
            <li>If you feel dizzy or unwell, contact the blood bank immediately.</li>
        </ul>
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">For Hospital Staff</h3>
        <p class="text-gray-600">
            - Verify donor eligibility and blood test results before collection.<br>
            - Ensure proper storage at 2–6°C for whole blood.<br>
            - Follow ISBT 128 standards for labeling blood units.<br>
            - Update donation status promptly in the system.
        </p>
